@page "/docs/introduction"
@namespace Lumeo.Docs.Pages.Docs

<PageTitle>Introduction — Lumeo</PageTitle>

<div class="space-y-10 max-w-3xl">

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground">Introduction</h1>
        <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Lumeo is a Blazor component library inspired by <a href="https://ui.shadcn.com" target="_blank" class="text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">shadcn/ui</a>,
            bringing the same philosophy of beautifully designed, accessible, and composable components to the .NET ecosystem.
            Built on top of Tailwind CSS v4 and targeting .NET 10, Lumeo gives you a complete set of UI primitives that
            you own and control — no black-box overrides, no style collisions.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Every component is designed with accessibility and developer experience in mind. Components are fully
            themeable via CSS variables, work seamlessly in both light and dark mode, and expose a consistent
            parameter API so you can drop them into any Blazor Server or WebAssembly project.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="border-t border-border"></div>

    <!-- Installation -->
    <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">Installation</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Install the NuGet package into your Blazor project:
        </p>

        <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">1. Add the package</h3>
            <div class="code-block rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted px-4 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-foreground">
                dotnet add package Lumeo
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">2. Register services</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">
                In your <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Program.cs</code>, register the Lumeo services:
            </p>
            <div class="code-block rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted px-4 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-foreground">
                builder.Services.AddLumeo();
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-3">3. Add global using</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">
                Add the namespace to your <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">_Imports.razor</code> so components are available everywhere:
            </p>
            <div class="code-block rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted px-4 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-foreground">
                @@using Lumeo
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="border-t border-border"></div>

    <!-- Usage -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">Usage</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Once installed, you can start using components directly in your <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">.razor</code> files.
            Here is a simple example using the <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Button</code> component:
        </p>
        <div class="code-block rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted px-4 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-foreground space-y-0.5">
            <div><span class="text-muted-foreground">&lt;!-- Default button --&gt;</span></div>
            <div>&lt;<span class="text-foreground">Button</span>&gt;Click me&lt;/<span class="text-foreground">Button</span>&gt;</div>
            <div class="pt-2"><span class="text-muted-foreground">&lt;!-- Variant and size --&gt;</span></div>
            <div>&lt;<span class="text-foreground">Button</span> <span class="text-muted-foreground">Variant</span>=<span class="text-foreground">"Button.ButtonVariant.Outline"</span> <span class="text-muted-foreground">Size</span>=<span class="text-foreground">"Button.ButtonSize.Sm"</span>&gt;</div>
            <div class="pl-4">Save changes</div>
            <div>&lt;/<span class="text-foreground">Button</span>&gt;</div>
            <div class="pt-2"><span class="text-muted-foreground">&lt;!-- With click handler --&gt;</span></div>
            <div>&lt;<span class="text-foreground">Button</span> <span class="text-muted-foreground">OnClick</span>=<span class="text-foreground">"HandleClick"</span>&gt;Submit&lt;/<span class="text-foreground">Button</span>&gt;</div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Every component accepts a <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Class</code> parameter for additional Tailwind classes
            and forwards any extra HTML attributes to the root element via <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">AdditionalAttributes</code>.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="border-t border-border"></div>

    <!-- Theming -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">Theming</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Lumeo uses CSS custom properties (variables) for all colors and design tokens. There are no hardcoded hex
            values or raw HSL colors anywhere in the component library. This means:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-base text-muted-foreground list-none">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-foreground shrink-0"></span>
                Dark mode works automatically via variable swaps — no <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">dark:</code> Tailwind prefixes needed.
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-foreground shrink-0"></span>
                You can swap the entire palette by overriding a handful of CSS variables in your own stylesheet.
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-foreground shrink-0"></span>
                Multiple built-in themes are available out of the box.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            See the <a href="themes" class="text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">Themes page</a> for
            a full list of available themes and instructions on creating your own custom theme.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="border-t border-border"></div>

    <!-- Components -->
    <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">Components</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Lumeo ships with 45+ components organized into six categories:
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">

            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-foreground">Form</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    Button, Input, Textarea, Select, Checkbox, Radio Group, Switch, Slider, Toggle, Toggle Group,
                    Label, OTP Input, Combobox, Date Picker, File Upload, Form.
                </p>
                <a href="components/button" class="text-sm text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">Browse Form components</a>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-foreground">Layout</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    Accordion, Aspect Ratio, Calendar, Card, Carousel, Collapsible, Resizable, Scroll Area,
                    Separator, Sidebar, Tabs.
                </p>
                <a href="components/card" class="text-sm text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">Browse Layout components</a>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-foreground">Feedback</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    Alert, Badge, Empty State, Progress, Skeleton, Spinner, Toast.
                </p>
                <a href="components/alert" class="text-sm text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">Browse Feedback components</a>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-foreground">Overlay</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    Alert Dialog, Command, Context Menu, Dialog, Drawer, Dropdown Menu, Hover Card, Popover,
                    Sheet, Tooltip.
                </p>
                <a href="components/dialog" class="text-sm text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">Browse Overlay components</a>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-foreground">Navigation</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    Breadcrumb, Menubar, Navigation Menu, Pagination.
                </p>
                <a href="components/breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">Browse Navigation components</a>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4 space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-foreground">Data Display</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    Avatar, Data Table, Table, Chart.
                </p>
                <a href="components/table" class="text-sm text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">Browse Data Display components</a>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>

</div>
